comments.body:
Then the constructor can't be made const (https://github.com/flutter/flutter/pull/39430). IMO the benefit of being able to make a const `CupertinoDynamicColor` and use it in a function as the default parameter outweighs the cost, e.g.
```dart
const Color _kDefaultColor = Color(...);
class ThumbPainter extends CustomPainter {
  const ThumbPainter({
     this.color = _kDefaultColor,
  }) : super(...);
}
```
Now if I want to make `_kDefaultColor` a `CupertinoDynamicColor`, without the const constructor I'll have to break the API. Also works better with NNBD.

